==Schedule==
The Jets' slate of regular season opponents was determined after the completion of the 2008 season. In addition to their traditional AFC East rivals, the team played opponents from the [[American Football Conference South Division|AFC South]] and [[National Football Conference South Division|NFC South]] divisions, and the third-place teams of the [[American Football Conference West Division|AFC West]] and [[American Football Conference North Division|AFC North]], as determined by the [[Regular season (NFL)|NFL scheduling formula]]. Their schedule was released in full on April 14.<ref name="schedule">{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=4068983|title=NFL releases full schedule|publisher=[[Associated Press]]|work=ESPN.com|date=April 14, 2009|accessdate=April 14, 2009}}</ref> Game times and channels from weeks 11, 12, and 14â17 were subject to change per the NFL's [[NFL on television#Flexible scheduling|flexible scheduling]] policy. Some controversy ensued over the placement of the Jets' first two home games, coinciding with the Jewish holidays of [[Rosh Hashanah]] and [[Yom Kippur]]. In response, the NFL moved the time of the game against the [[Tennessee Titans]] to 1:00&nbsp;pm Eastern.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=4078103|title=Jets to play Titans at 1&nbsp;pm in Week 3|publisher=[[Associated Press]]|work=ESPN.com|date=April 17, 2009|accessdate=April 18, 2009}}</ref> The Jets played a regular season game outside the United States for the first time when they played the Bills in Toronto; the game is the second in a five-year series of regular and preseason games the Bills are playing at the [[Rogers Centre]].<ref name="Toronto">{{cite web|url=http://www.torontosun.com/sports/football/2009/04/15/9115316-sun.html|title=Bills Toronto date is with the Jets|author=Fidlin, Ken|publisher=[[Toronto Sun]]|date=April 15, 2009|accessdate=April 18, 2009|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5iids1seK|archivedate=August 2, 2009|deadurl=no}}</ref>

All games will be broadcast on [[WEPN|1050AM ESPN]] except for Week 13.

