==Game summaries==
===Week 1: at Houston Texans===
{{Americanfootballbox|
|Road='''Jets'''
|R1=3||R2=7||R3=7||R4=7
|Home=Texans
|H1=0||H2=0||H3=0||H4=7
|stadium= [[Reliant Stadium]], [[Houston, Texas]]
|time= 1:00&nbsp;pm [[North American Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]
|weather= 77 Â°F (Partly Cloudy)<ref name="week 1 gb">{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/54473/HST_Gamebook.pdf|title=New York Jets at Houston Texans Gamebook|publisher=National Football League|date=September 13, 2009|accessdate=November 10, 2009}}</ref>
|attendance= 70,118<ref name="week 1 gb"/>
|referee= [[Ed Hochuli]]<ref name="week 1 gb"/>
|TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]] |TVAnnouncers= [[Jim Nantz]] & [[Phil Simms]]
}}
The Jets began their season at [[Reliant Stadium]] for a Week 1 showdown with the [[Houston Texans]].  New York took off in the first quarter as kicker [[Jay Feely]] nailed a 24-yard field goal.  In the second quarter, the Jets would increase their lead as rookie quarterback [[Mark Sanchez]] completed his first career touchdown pass as he connected with wide receiver [[Chansi Stuckey]] on a 30-yard pass.  In the third quarter, New York continued their run as running back [[Thomas Jones (American football)|Thomas Jones]] got a 1-yard touchdown run.  The Texans tried to rally in the fourth quarter as safety [[Dominique Barber]] returned a fumble 48 yards for a touchdown, but the Jets would end the game with Jones getting a 38-yard touchdown run.

With the win, not only did New York begin their season at 1â0, but Sanchez (18-of-31, 272 yards, 1 TD, 1 INT) would become the 1st Jets rookie QB since [[Richard Todd (American football)|Richard Todd]] in 1976 to win a game.

