===Week 6: vs. Buffalo Bills===
{{Americanfootballbox|
|Road='''Bills'''
|R1=3||R2=0||R3=10||R4=0||R5=3
|Home=Jets
|H1=3||H2=10||H3=0||H4=0||H5=0
|stadium= [[Giants Stadium]], [[East Rutherford, New Jersey]]
|time= 4:15&nbsp;pm [[North American Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]
|weather= 44 Â°F (Cloudy)<ref name="week 6 gb">{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/54554/NYJ_Gamebook.pdf|title=Buffalo Bills at New York Jets Gamebook|publisher=National Football League|date=October 18, 2009|accessdate=November 10, 2009}}</ref>
|attendance= 76,048<ref name="week 6 gb"/>
|referee= [[Walt Coleman]]<ref name="week 6 gb"/>
|TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]] |TVAnnouncers= [[Dick Enberg]] & [[Dan Fouts]]
}}
Hoping to snap a two-game losing streak, the Jets went home for a Week 6 AFC East duel with the [[Buffalo Bills]].  Both teams began the first quarter with field goals, as Bills kicker [[Rian Lindell]] made a 33-yard field goal and Jets kicker [[Jay Feely]] getting a 23-yard field goal.  In the second quarter, New York soared into the lead with Feely's 41-yard field goal and running back [[Thomas Jones (American football)|Thomas Jones]]' 71-yard touchdown run.  However, Buffalo rallied to tie the game in the third quarter with Lindell's 25-yard field goal and quarterback [[Ryan Fitzpatrick]]'s 37-yard touchdown pass to wide receiver [[Lee Evans (American football)|Lee Evans]].  After both teams failed to get any point in the fourth quarter, the game went into overtime.  Despite getting the ball to start off OT, the Jets failed to get any point out of their opening drive.  After a hard-fought period, the Bills would emerge on top as Lindell booted the game-winning 47-yard field goal.

With the loss, New York fell to 3â3.

Thomas Jones would have a career day as he ran 22 times for a franchise-best 210 yards (in addition to his rushing touchdown).

